              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Hydraulic Conveyer in the Kyoto University",
                "Research Reactor(KUR) . KUR was operated at the",
                "thermal power of 5 MW."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cs-137 standard solution, Code# CS005, which was",
                "supplied by JRIA was used for the samples. Cs-135 was",
                "included as an impurity in the Cs-137 standard",
                "solution. Two Cs-137 standard solutions equivalent to",
                "about 200 Bq were prepared. The isotope ratios of",
                "Cs-135 to Cs-137 were determined with TIMS.",
                "Bare target: Cs-135/Cs-137 = 0.8970 +- 0.00024",
                "Gd Shield:   Cs-135/Cs-137 = 0.8990 +- 0.00014"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Cadmium-difference method. To set",
                " 0.133 eV as cut-off energy, Gd foils with thickness",
                "of 25 um was used as neutron filter. Wires of Au/Al",
                "alloy and Co/Al alloy were used to monitor neutron",
                "fluxes. A set of the samples with and without the Gd",
                "filters were used for the experiments.",
                "Irradiations for the bare and Gd filtered targets",
                "were performed for 3 and 6 h, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " High purity germanium detector, relative",
                "efficiency of 70% and 1.9 keV FWHM at the 1.33 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The activities of Cs-137, Cs-136 and monitor wires",
                "were measured by gamma-ray spectroscopy. Neutron flux",
                "was deduced from the activities of the wires. (tables",
                "2 and 3 in the REFERENCE) Deduced neutron flux: (e+14",
                "n/cm2/sec) Thermal neutron Epi-thermal neutron Bare",
                "target: 1.07 +-0.03 0.313+-0.021 Gd Shield:",
                "0.155+-0.006 0.426+-0.012 The main contribution of",
                "the uncertainties came from uncertainties due to",
                "abundance of Co and Au in the wires and the detection",
                "effeciency of the Ge detector. On the basis of",
                "Westcott's convention, the cross section was derived",
                "from the activity ratio of Cs-136 to Cs-137, the",
                "half-lives of Cs-136 and Cs-137, the isotopic ratio",
                "of Cs-135 to Cs-137 in the sample, and the neutron",
                "fluxes."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The peak detection efficiencies were determined with",
                "a set of calibrated mixed sources: Cd-109, Co-57,",
                "Ce-139, Sn-113, Cs-137, Y-88, and Co-60."
              ]
            }
          ],
